snippet.textDisplay:
Omg! That was so brilliant to watch. Big fan of coke studio and a bigger fan of Amit Trivedi.
First up, I absolutely loved Mr. Mustn't voice. Amazing. I love Rajasthani folk music but a contemporary take by Mr. Trivedi? Seriously, whole new level!
You could see that everyone out there was having such a great time and it is just awesome to watch that and hear the great music that comes out of that.
The only thing that sort of soured my experience, I hope Coke Studio is taking notes  :-P, is that they messed up the transaction real bad.
Daal Baati is a regional meal, MEAL! Daal is lentils and baati is made of baked dough. Thank you Mr. translator. It is NOT a sweet dish. I think the translator was referring to churma which usually accompanies the duo.
Anyway, great performance! Loved it!
P.S you guys have a great thing going, why mess that up because of such an obvious and avoidable error.
